## 📝 How to reference this license

### In your README.md:
```markdown
## License

This project is licensed under the MIT License - see the [LICENSE](LICENSE) file for details.

Copyright (c) 2024 Wei Liu
```

### In package metadata (setup.py):
```python
setup(
    name='ledom-layouter',
    version='1.2.3',
    license='MIT',
    author='Wei Liu',
    author_email='liuwei71320@example.com',
    url='https://github.com/liuwei71320/ledom-layouter',
    classifiers=[
        'License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License',
        'Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9+',
    ],
)
```

### In your source code headers:
```python
"""
Ledom Layouter v1.2.3
Copyright (c) 2024 Wei Liu (liuwei71320)
Licensed under the MIT License.
See LICENSE file for details.
"""
```

